# GRE (RFC 2784) over IPv4 (IP protocol 47), no flags, protocol type 0x0800 — tunneling a bare inner
# IPv4/ICMP packet. Exercises typed-tunnel dispatch: GRE's protocolType routes the inner to IPv4 (which
# accepts a 'gre' parent), NOT the EthernetII fallback.
# source: standard GRE header + a real inner IP packet emitted via a raw IPPROTO_GRE socket to 127.0.0.1
# on a debian:12 container's ethernet lo, captured with tcpdump.
